  note = {This book chapter argues that when charts update, animating the transition helps maintain object constancy. It suggests keeping animations between 250~ms and 2~s: shorter animations may be hard to follow, while longer ones may frustrate users. The authors also recommend announcing changes to screen reader users.}
}